  "prompt": "Which are the top 5 Bollywood songs of 2015?",
  "response": "In 2015, Bollywood delivered a plethora of memorable and chart-topping songs that captivated audiences across India and beyond. Here are the top 5 Bollywood songs of that year:\n\n1. **\"Gerua\"** \u2013 *Dilwale*\n   - **Singer:** Arijit Singh & Antara Mitra\n   - **Composer:** Pritam\n   - **Description:** A visually stunning romantic track featuring Shah Rukh Khan and Kajol, \"Gerua\" became an instant favorite for its melodious tune and picturesque music video shot in Iceland.\n\n2. **\"Banno\"** \u2013 *Tanu Weds Manu Returns*\n   - **Singer:** Shreya Ghoshal & Vishal Dadlani\n   - **Composer:** Krsna Solo\n   - **Description:** This energetic and vibrant song celebrates the bride's beauty and traditions, becoming a staple at weddings and parties for its catchy beats and lively choreography.\n\n3. **\"Tere Bin\"** \u2013 *Wazir*\n   - **Singer:** Rahat Fateh Ali Khan & Tulsi Kumar\n   - **Composer:** Amaal Mallik\n   - **Description:** A soulful and emotional track that highlights deep romantic longing, \"Tere Bin\" resonated with listeners for its heartfelt lyrics and powerful vocals.\n\n4. **\"Pani Da Rang\"** \u2013 *Vicky Donor*\n   - **Singer:** Ayushmann Khurrana\n   - **Composer:** Ayushmann Khurrana & Shabbir Ahmed\n   - **Description:** Though originally released earlier, this song continued its popularity into 2015 with its fresh take on love and its soothing melody, performed by the film's lead actor.\n\n5. **\"Prem Ratan Dhan Payo\"** \u2013 *Prem Ratan Dhan Payo*\n   - **Singer:** Palak Muchhal\n   - **Composer:** Himesh Reshammiya\n   - **Description:** The title track of the Salman Khan starrer became a festive favorite, known for its grand orchestration and uplifting lyrics celebrating love and prosperity.\n\nThese songs not only topped the music charts but also left a lasting impact on Bollywood music, showcasing a blend of romantic melodies, energetic beats, and soulful performances that defined the musical landscape of 2015.",
